<div class="accordion-wrapper">
    <h3 class="accordion-title">Glycolic Acid 7% Exfoliating Toner FAQs</h3>

    <div class="accordion-section">
        <div class="accordion-header">
            <div class="usage-toggle-icon icon-up_chevron">
                <h3 class="accordion-question">What does Glycolic Acid 7% Exfoliating Toner do for the skin?</h3>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="accordion-content collapse">
            <span class="accordion-answer">
                The Ordinary Glycolic Acid 7% Toning Solution is an exfoliating toner designed to gently remove dead skin cells, promoting the appearance of a brighter and more even skin tone. This formulation also helps improve skin texture, reducing the appearance of fine lines.
            </span>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="accordion-section">
        <div class="accordion-header">
            <div class="usage-toggle-icon icon-up_chevron">
                <h3 class="accordion-question">How often should I use Glycolic Acid 7% Exfoliating Toner?</h3>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="accordion-content collapse">
            <span class="accordion-answer">
                The Glycolic Acid 7% Toning Solution can be used once daily, ideally in your PM routine. However, if you are new to chemical exfoliants or direct acids, it’s recommended that you start with 2-3 times a week and gradually increase the frequency as your skin builds tolerance.
            </span>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="accordion-section">
        <div class="accordion-header">
            <div class="usage-toggle-icon icon-up_chevron">
                <h3 class="accordion-question">Can I use Glycolic Acid 7% Exfoliating Toner with other acids or retinoids?</h3>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="accordion-content collapse">
            <span class="accordion-answer">
                Do not use the Glycolic Acid 7% Toning Solution with other direct acids (like salicylic acid) or strong retinoids in the same routine, as this can increase the risk of irritation. Instead, alternate use or use one set of formulations in the AM and the other in the PM.
            </span>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="accordion-section">
        <div class="accordion-header">
            <div class="usage-toggle-icon icon-up_chevron">
                <h3 class="accordion-question">Is Glycolic Acid 7% Exfoliating Toner suitable for all skin types?</h3>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="accordion-content collapse">
            <span class="accordion-answer">
                We do not recommend using this formulation on sensitive, peeling, or compromised skin. If you have concerns about sensitivity, consider doing a <a href="https://theordinary.com/patch-test">patch test</a> before full application.
            </span>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="accordion-section">
        <div class="accordion-header">
            <div class="usage-toggle-icon icon-up_chevron">
                <h3 class="accordion-question">What precautions should I take when using The Ordinary Glycolic Acid 7% Exfoliating Toner?</h3>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="accordion-content collapse">
            <span class="accordion-answer">
                The Ordinary Glycolic Acid 7% Toning Solution contains an alpha hydroxy acid (AHA) that can increase your skin's sensitivity to sunlight and put you at risk of sunburn. We strongly recommend using sunscreen, wearing protective clothing, or limiting sun exposure while using this formulation.
            </span>
        </div>
    </div>
